<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Rapidly SDK privacy manifest.

        Apple requires SDKs that use "required-reason" APIs to ship a
        PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy declaring those uses, otherwise customer
        App Store submissions are rejected with ITMS-91056.

        The engine binary uses stat() / fstat() to check file existence
        and read model file sizes before loading. These fall under the
        FileTimestamp category. Reason C617.1 covers "Access the
        timestamps, size, or other metadata of files inside the app
        container, app group container, or the app's CloudKit
        container" -- which is what the SDK does on a customer-
        supplied model file path.

        No tracking, no data collection. The SDK is fully on-device.

        AUDIT (post-PR-92 cleanup, CL-5): `nm -u` was run against all
        three shipped slices (macOS universal, iOS arm64, iOS Simulator
        universal). The only required-reason API symbols imported are
        _stat / _fstat (FileTimestamp, declared below). No System Boot
        Time (mach_absolute_time / mach_continuous_time / clock_gettime),
        Disk Space (statfs / statvfs / getfsstat), or User Defaults
        (NSUserDefaults / CFPreferences) symbols are present. The engine
        does call wall-clock time() / std::chrono::system_clock::now(),
        but those are NOT on Apple's required-reason list (that list's
        time category covers only uptime APIs, not calendar time). This
        manifest is therefore complete as of this audit.

        MAINTENANCE CONTRACT: when adding engine source that calls a
        required-reason API -- mach_absolute_time / mach_continuous_time
        (System Boot Time, 35F9.1), statfs / statvfs / getfsstat (Disk
        Space, E174.1 / 85F4.1), NSUserDefaults / CFPreferences (User
        Defaults, CA92.1 / 1C8F.1), etc. -- add the matching
        NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType entry below with the appropriate
        NSPrivacyAccessedAPIReasons code BEFORE shipping. A miss is not
        caught at our build time; it surfaces as an opaque ITMS-91056
        rejection on the customer's App Store submission. Re-run the
        `nm -u` audit above whenever the engine's syscall surface
        changes. Apple's full required-reason API list:
        https://developer.apple.com/documentation/bundleresources/privacy_manifest_files/describing_use_of_required_reason_api
    -->
    <key>NSPrivacyTracking</key>
    <false/>
    <key>NSPrivacyTrackingDomains</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyCollectedDataTypes</key>
    <array/>
    <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPITypes</key>
    <array>
        <dict>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIType</key>
            <string>NSPrivacyAccessedAPICategoryFileTimestamp</string>
            <key>NSPrivacyAccessedAPIReasons</key>
            <array>
                <string>C617.1</string>
            </array>
        </dict>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
